# Checkpoint 2 Results

**Date:** 2026-05-21  
**Team:** Financial Fraud Detection Group  
**Project:** AI Capstone Financial Fraud Detection System  
**Component Focus:** End-to-End Integration Test  

---

## End-to-End Status: PARTIAL

The system is partially working. Transaction records exist in Airtable, AI Core processing has successfully filled AI output fields, and fraud investigation case records exist for suspicious transactions. However, the full end-to-end pipeline still needs to be confirmed using one single record in the same Airtable base from start to finish.

The main issue is that there appear to be multiple Airtable base copies or views being used. Some tables show the original transaction records, another table shows AI Core results, and another table shows fraud investigation case records. Because of that, the checkpoint is marked **PARTIAL** instead of **PASSED**.

---

## Test Record Used

For this checkpoint test, the project used existing financial fraud transaction records from Airtable, including suspicious records such as:

| Transaction ID | Amount | Transaction Type | Status / Result |
|---|---:|---|---|
| TXN-0007 | 67.45 | payment | case_created |
| TXN-0014 | 875.60 | transfer | case_created |
| TXN-0019 | 7800.00 | transfer | case_created |

These records were used because they already show suspicious activity moving into case records.

